title: Roald Dahl - Kiss Kiss
description:
Kiss Kiss

Written by Roald Dahl 

Read by Tamsin Greig, Juliet Stevenson, Stephanie Beacham, Adrian Scarborough, Derek Jacobi, Stephen Mangan 


Released by  Penguin Books in 2013 

UNABRIDGED

Length: 9 hours


This is an unabridged audiobook edition of Roald Dahl's 'Kiss Kiss', a dark collection of short stories for adults.

What could go wrong when a wife pawns the mink coat that her lover gave her as a parting gift? What happens when a priceless piece of furniture is the subject of a deceitful bargain? Can a wronged woman take revenge on her dead husband? In these dark, disturbing stories Roald Dahl explores the sinister side of human nature: the cunning, sly, selfish part of each of us that leads us into the territory of the unexpected and unsettling. Stylish, macabre and haunting, these tales will leave you with a delicious feeling of unease.


The stories are:

The Landlady,  read by Tamsin Greig
William and Mary,  read by Juliet Stevenson & Adrian Scarborough
The Way up to Heaven,  read by Stephanie Beacham
Parson's Pleasure,  read by Derek Jacobi
Mrs Bixby and the Colonel's Coat,  read by Stephanie Beacham
Royal Jelly,  read by Adrian Scarborough
Georgy Porgy,  read by Derek Jacobi
Genesis and Catastrophe,  read by Juliet Stevenson
Edward the Conquerer,  read by Juliet Stevenson
Pig,  read by Stephanie Beacham
The Champion of the World,  read by Stephen Mangan



File format:  mp3  (64 Kbps, 24 KHz, 2 Channels, Joint Stereo)
